/**
\mainpage Graphical User Interface module.

\bdesc
This module aims to provide a GUI feature to your programs.

\ddesc
It uses a C++ API to build a inner representation of your GUI panels. The
display is assumed by a remote java process that interprets XML document on
the fly. The connection is handled on a TCP/IP socket. You can find much more information about the java gui
in the ( not yet standardized ) XmlBasedGui cvs module.
Actually, there is no dynamic link to update widgets from the server point of view.

\ex
This code makes appear a simple window with few widgets.
\code
// will be updated
\endcode

<h2> Widget's status </h2>

<h3> Running widgets </h3>
<ul>
<li> Windows - gwtWINDOW </li>
<li> Textfields - gwtTEXTFIELD </li>
<li> Buttons - gwtBUTTON </li>
<li> Tables - gwtTABLE </li>
<li> Separator - gwtSEPARATOR </li>
</ul>

<h3> Comming widgets </h3>
<ul>
<li> Menus - gwtMENU gwtMENUITEM </li>
<li> Labels - gwtLABEL </li>
<li> Checkboxes - gwtCHECKBOX </li>
<li> Multichoice </li>
<li> Slider - gwtSLIDER </li>
</ul>

\n
 */
